8  |  DISCOVERY QUESTIONS — Surface Sertica's weaknesses naturally

Ask without naming Sertica. Expose gaps that favour AMOS™.

•	How important is it that your system is approved by your specific classification society — and do you operate vessels under more than one class?
•	When you scale — by acquiring vessels, entering new regions, or adding business units — how do you expect your platform to keep up without re-implementation?
•	How does the vendor handle crewing and payroll — is that native to the platform, or does it involve a separate vendor?
•	What are the vendor's support hours outside their primary office timezone — especially for 24/7 operations?
•	Where is your operational data hosted, and who controls it? Does it sit within a region your compliance requirements demand?
•	Who owns the software vendor — and how does the parent's commercial interests align with your operational roadmap?
•	If you needed board-level governance reporting across multiple entities and regions simultaneously, have you seen it demonstrated at that scale?
•	What is your current three-way invoice match rate — and what does a failed match cost you in investigation time?
•	How much procurement spend variance do you carry per quarter — and can you see it in real time at the point of approval?

